# Graph updates (immutability)

Every change yields a **new** graph reference. Never mutate `NodeGraph`, its `nodes` / `connections` / `viewState` / `automation`, or node `parameters` in place.

- **Use** `src/data-model/immutableUpdates.ts` (`updateNodeParameter`, `addNode`, `addConnection`, `updateViewState`, …) or **`graphStore`** actions (they wrap helpers). Pass the updated graph into runtime afterward.
- **Don’t:** `graph.nodes.find(...).parameters[x] = …`; user-driven changes bypassing the store.

**Refs:** `immutableUpdates.ts`, `docs/architecture/graph-and-platform-boundaries.md` (graph ownership).
